# Source to Client and Contract Sync

When changes are made to the main code in `src/`, keep the npm client and contract tests aligned with the new API/spec behavior.

## Required updates

1. If API endpoints are added or changed, update the client library in `client/` (`SimpleVaultClient` and types).
2. If behavior/spec changes are relevant, update contract tests in `client/test/` (run against the Rust binary via `run-with-rust-server.mjs` or a running server).

## Completion checklist

- [ ] `client/` updated for endpoint/API changes
- [ ] `client/test/` contract tests updated when behavior/spec changed
